The more I think about it, the more I like this design because it doesn’t add another specialist. It adds a governor. In operating systems, CPU schedulers don’t perform the work themselves—they decide which processes get resources and when. Mara plays an analogous role for the Pantheon: allocating cognitive “resolution” across the existing daemons so each operates at the level of detail that best matches the current task. That makes the whole architecture more coordinated without making it more complicated.